    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan for `uv cache stats`:\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**4 files touched, 1 file created.**\n\n### Step 1 — `crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`\n- **Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` variant** to `CacheCommand` enum after the existing `Size(SizeArgs),` (line 904)\n- **Add `StatsArgs` struct** after `SizeArgs` (line 952) — identical shape to `SizeArgs` with the same `--human`/`-H`/`--human-readable` flag\n\n### Step 2 — `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs` *(new file)*\n- Modeled after `cache_size.rs`, but loops over `CacheBucket::iter()` (10 variants, `Python` excluded by design)\n- For each bucket: resolves the path via `Cache::bucket(bucket)`, measures with `DiskUsage::new(vec![path]).count_ignoring_errors()`, accumulates the total\n- Prints `{bucket}: {size}` per line using `CacheBucket`'s `Display` impl (e.g. `wheels-v6`, `sdists-v9`)\n- Prints `total: {size}` at the end\n- Handles the case where the cache root doesn't exist (prints all zeros)\n- No `preview` parameter — not required\n\n### Step 3 — `crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`\n- Add `mod cache_stats;` after `mod cache_size;` (line 84)\n- Add `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;` after `pub(crate) use cache_size::cache_size;` (line 21)\n\n### Step 4 — `crates/uv/src/lib.rs`\n- Add dispatch arm for `CacheCommand::Stats(args)` right after the `CacheCommand::Size` arm (line 1181), calling `commands::cache_stats(&cache, args.human, printer)` (no `await`, no `preview`)",
